            <p>When you come across inflected infinitives, look at the context to see how they should best be
                translated.
                Often 'in order to' is the best translation, but use the rest of the sentence to help you out.
                In the second sentence above, there is an obligation being expressed (it is <em>most needful</em>), and here a simple translation 'to hold' makes most sense.
            </p>
